        <div class="portfolio-desc">
            <p>PinocchioVR is a virtual reality game that explores the in-the-headset and out-of-headset experience. The viewer is Pinocchio, trapped in a whale's stomach. Those waiting in line to try the VR experience can walk up to a microphone and ask the viewer questions. These questions are ported into the game as the whale's voice, and a heart sensor detects slight changes in pulse to detect whether Pinocchio's answers are the truth or a lie. Answer questions truthfully before the whale blows you out of its blowhole to escape and become a real boy!</p>
            <p>In collaboration with DongChan Kim and Anastasis Germanidis. Special thanks to Todd Bryant.</p>
            <p>This piece was shown at the NYU ITP Show Spring 2017.</p>  
